    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.03157.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date rend="right">Monday morning<ptr target="loc.03157_n1"/></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Walt,</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I had proposed to be over yesterday, but the rain set in, &#38; <unclear
                    reason="illegible" resp="#smb" cert="low">minus an umbrella</unclear>. I
                concluded to stay home &amp; paint. I have the President about finished off.<ptr
                    target="loc.03157_n2"/> Hope to cast him, for good or ill, Wednesday, &#38; get
                him on exhibition.</p>
            <p>I have painted 2 heads of yourself, &#38; <pb xml:id="leaf001v"
                    facs="loc.03157.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/> will bring them over. Have not
                been very well, so have had to keep quiet &#38; stay <choice>
                    <orig>in doors</orig>
                    <reg>indoors</reg>
                </choice>, in order to put in some time at work. I think the president looks <hi
                    rend="underline">well</hi>. I wish if it is a pleasant day tomorrow, you would
                get up courage ride over &#38; make a call, &#38; see <pb xml:id="leaf002r"
                    facs="loc.03157.003_large.jpg" type="recto"/> for yourself how the "head (&#38;
                body) of the Nation looks."</p>
            <p>The boxes were shipped Monday, &#38; I suppose you may have heard from Dr Bucke.<ptr
                    target="n0119"/></p>

            <p>Tell Mrs. Davis<ptr target="n6113"/> to look after the "hens &#38; things" in the
                back yard &#38; I will be greatly obliged. I sent Smith <pb xml:id="leaf002v"
                    facs="loc.03157.004_large.jpg" type="verso"/> with your bust,<ptr
                    target="loc.02912_n3"/> an Emerson<ptr target="loc.03157_n3"/> &#38; two of the
                medallions.</p>
            <p>I hope you are as well as usual.</p>
            <p>If Herbert comes in today or tomorrow, ask him if <choice>
                    <orig>wont</orig>
                    <reg>won't</reg>
                </choice> come &#38; see me at <hi rend="underline">136 N. 17</hi>. </p>

            <p>This rain will settle things for the big Centennial&#8212;</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                <signed rend="right">S. H. Morse.</signed>
            </closer>

